Decomposition of the series¶

In [10]:
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose
decomposition = seasonal_decompose(lair)

trend = decomposition.trend
seasonal = decomposition.seasonal
residual = decomposition.resid

fig, ax = plt.subplots(4,1,figsize=(12,12))
plt.subplot(411)
plt.plot(lair, label='Original')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.subplot(412)
plt.plot(trend, label='Trend')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.subplot(413)
plt.plot(seasonal,label='Seasonality')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.subplot(414)
plt.plot(residual, label='Residuals')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.tight_layout()

lags=50
data = lair

# take the first regular difference
data = lair - lair.shift(1)
data.dropna(inplace=True)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,6))
fig = sgt.plot_acf(data, ax=ax[0], lags=lags, alpha=alpha, unbiased=True)
fig = sgt.plot_pacf(data, ax=ax[1], lags=lags, alpha=alpha, method='ols')

data = lair - lair.shift(12)
data.dropna(inplace=True)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,6))
fig = sgt.plot_acf(data, ax=ax[0], lags=lags, alpha=alpha, unbiased=True)

In [20]:
# take the first regular and seasonal difference
data = lair - lair.shift(1) - (lair.shift(12) - lair.shift(13))
data.dropna(inplace=True)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,6))
fig = sgt.plot_acf(data, ax=ax[0], lags=lags, alpha=alpha, unbiased=True)
fig = sgt.plot_pacf(data, ax=ax[1], lags=lags, alpha=alpha, method='ols')

Nonseasonal modeling¶

In [25]:
from statsmodels.tsa.arima_model import ARIMA
# initial fit of the model without seasonal component
model = ARIMA(data, order=(1, 0, 1))  
results_ns = model.fit(disp=-1) 
print(results_ns.summary())

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
plt.plot(data, label='Original')
plt.plot(results_ns.fittedvalues, color='red', label='fitted')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.title('RSS: %.4f'% sum((results_ns.fittedvalues-data['Passengers'].values)**2))

In [22]:
# map the prediction in the original space
L=12;
pred = lair.copy();
pred.loc[data.index,'Passengers'] = results_ns.fittedvalues
# the first few samples are used as initial values
allday = pred.index;
for day in data.index:
    # get the index of the day
    idx = allday.get_loc(day);
    pred.iloc[idx] = pred.iloc[idx] + lair.iloc[idx-1] + lair.iloc[idx-L] - lair.iloc[idx-L-1];

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
plt.plot(lair, label='Original')
plt.plot(pred, color='red', label='fitted')
plt.legend(loc='best')

<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x11d6c95f8>
